0that%20the%20use%20of%20the%20rapidly%20advancing%20technology%20won't%20kill%20off%20the%20billable%20hour%20payment%20model%2C%20but%20rather%20reinvent%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20attorneys%20said%20that%20as%20AI%20tools%20are%20used%20at%20firms%20to%20automate%20routine%20and%20time-consuming%20grunt%20work%20tasks%20like%20document%20review%20and%20due%20diligence%2C%20the%20number%20of%20billable%20hours%20to%20a%20client%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20reduced%2C%20and%20the%20value%20of%20a%20lawyer's%20individual%20hour%20is%20likely%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20value%20that%20lawyers%20provide%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20that's%20strategic%20advice%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20the%20actual%20drafting%20of%20arguments%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20the%20arguing%20in%20court%20to%20jurors%20or%20to%20judges%20in%20courtrooms%2C%20or%20to%20the%20making%20of%20deals%20and%20negotiating%20terms%20%E2%80%94%20all%20those%20sorts%20of%20things%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20an%20increasing%20premium%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michel%20Paradis%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20global%20firm%20Curtis%2C%20Mallet-Prevost%2C%20Colt%20%26amp%3B%20Mosle%20LLP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParadis%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20AI-related%20legal%20work%20and%20also%20teaches%20national%20security%20and%20constitutional%20law%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School%2C%20said%20he%20doesn't%20believe%20there%20will%20ever%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20disappearance%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-sonnedix-legal-eliminated-billable-hour-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebillable%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20law%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20think%20you're%20likely%20to%20see%20is%20a%20slow%20disappearance%20of%20the%20filler%20billable%20hours%26quot%3B%20that%20a%20slew%20of%20law%20firms%20depend%20on%2C%20Paradis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20way%20that%20the%20introduction%20of%20word%20processors%20dramatically%20shifted%20the%20way%20law%20firms%20operated%20in%20the%20late%2020th%20century%2C%20Paradis%20said%20he%20foresees%20the%20same%20thing%20happening%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20going%20to%20have%20a%20similar%20effect%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20information%20technology%20in%20the%20legal%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Paradis%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20is%20a%20consistent%20gobbling%20up%20of%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20legal%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElisa%20Botero%2C%20another%20partner%20at%20the%20New%20York-headquartered%20firm%2C%20agreed%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20billable%20hour%20model%20will%20remain%20a%20%26quot%3Bkey%20metric%26quot%3B%20for%20at%20least%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20even%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-law-firms-using-ai-fast-track-ma-deals-work-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20law%20firms%20move%20to%20utilize%20AI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20boost%20the%20efficiency%20of%20their%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20what%20type%20of%20work%20will%20be%20billed%20out%20will%20shift%20and%20is%20already%20shifting%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Botero%2C%20explaining%20that%20more%20traditional%2C%20associate-type%20work%20or%20junior-level%20work%20will%20be%20most%20impacted%20by%20the%20use%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou'll%20still%20see%20billable%20hours%2C%20but%20you'll%20see%20a%20reduction%20of%20those%20billable%20hours%20for%20that%20type%20of%20routine%20legal%20work%20that%20can%20be%20automated%26quot%3B%20with%20AI%20tools%2C%20Botero%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2266e39611-3337-4510-85b9-68f507694c7f%5C%22%3EAI%20can't%20replace%20everything%20a%20lawyer%20does%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Gatto%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Sheppard%20Mullin%20who%20co-leads%20the%20firm's%20AI%20industry%20team%20of%20about%20100%20attorneys%2C%20said%20that%20the%20billable%20hour%20isn't%20going%20anywhere%20for%20higher-level%20work%2C%20but%20that%20there%20may%20be%20a%20fixed-rate%20payment%20for%20legal%20services%20that%20are%20primarily%20done%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20using%20AI%20to%20produce%20a%20draft%20of%20a%20brief%20that%20would%20have%20taken%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20%245%2C000%20of%20legal%20time%20to%20do%20a%20first%20draft%2C%20maybe%20now%20it's%20%242%2C500%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatto%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20AI%20%26quot%3Bmay%20accelerate%20the%20elimination%20or%20minimization%20of%20billable%20hours%20for%20certain%20types%20of%20work%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20will%20do%20it%20across%20the%20board.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20everything%20that%20a%20lawyer%20does%20can%20be%20replaced%20by%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20attorney%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20legal%20work%20involving%20depositions%2C%20trials%2C%20negotiations%2C%20and%20mediations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrank%20Gerratana%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20international%20firm%20Mintz%2C%20Levin%2C%20Cohn%2C%20Ferris%2C%20Glovsky%20and%20Popeo%2C%20P.C.%2C%20said%20that%20he%20sees%20the%20integration%20of%20AI%20tools%20in%20law%20firms%20as%20a%20positive%20that%20can%20allow%20attorneys%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20on%20critical%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20envision%20a%20scenario%20in%20which%20lawyers%20can%20simply%20charge%20more%20per%20hour%20because%20they're%20spending%20more%20time%20on%20the%20highest%20value%20work%20and%20things%20that%20are%20time-consuming%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20particularly%20high%20value%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20automated%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gerratana%2C%20who%20advises%20clients%20on%20intellectual%20property%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20integration%20of%20AI%20into%20law%20firms%2C%20Gerratana%20said%20he%20can%20picture%20a%20world%20where%20hour-based%20billing%2C%20subscription-type%20billing%2C%20and%20task-based%20billing%20for%20legal%20services%20all%20exist%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%2C%20as%20an%20attorney%2C%20can%20really%20speed%20up%20my%20work%20I%20might%20be%20more%20inclined%26quot%3B%20to%20bill%20by%20the%20task%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf826b9d-4af6-4b2e-b1a7-362abf3e58f6%5C%22%3EA%202023%20ABA%20survey%20found%20that%2020%25%20of%20law%20firms%20were%20using%20or%20considering%20using%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanbar.org%2Fgroups%2Flaw_practice%2Fresources%2Ftech-report%2F2023%2F2023-artificial-intelligence-ai-techreport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fis-law-school-worth-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Bar%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2010.9%25%20of%20firms%20across%20all%20sizes%20were%20using%20AI%20tools%20in%20their%20practices%2C%20while%209.8%25%20were%20seriously%20considering%20purchasing%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGatto%20said%20that%20his%20firm%20utilizes%20a%20custom%20AI%20tool%20that%20was%20developed%20in-house.%20The%20tool%20can%20be%20used%20to%20draft%20legal%20memos%20and%20briefs%20and%20to%20create%20initial%20agreements%20of%20all%20kinds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%20any%20type%20of%20legal%20document%2C%20you%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20at%20least%20right%20now%2C%20to%20assist%20in%20creating%20a%20first%20draft%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatto%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20Sheppard%20Mullin%20is%20still%20currently%20charging%20clients%20by%20the%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20part%20that's%20being%20done%20by%20AI%2C%20we're%20charging%20still%20just%20hourly.%20If%20it%20takes%20five%20minutes%2C%20we%20bill%20five%20minutes%2C%20that's%20it%2C%20but%20none%20of%20that%20stuff%20is%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20the%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gatto%2C%20explaining%20that%20an%20initial%20draft%20of%20a%20document%20created%20with%20the%20help%20of%20AI%20would%20be%20comparable%20to%20the%20work%20of%20a%20first-year%20law%20school%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20work%20that%20gets%20done%20between%20the%20partner%20and%20the%20first%20year%20to%20get%20the%20memo%20to%20the%20point%20where%20it%20takes%20everything%20into%20account%20and%20it's%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20a%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatto%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firms%20Curtis%20and%20Mintz%20are%20still%20in%20the%20piloting%20phase%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20use%20of%20AI%20in%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20law%20firm%20that%20is%20not%20currently%20investigating%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20tools%20in%20their%20practice%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20quickly%20behind%20the%20law%20firms%20that%20have%20figured%20this%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gerratana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJuan%20Perla%2C%20another%20partner%20at%20Curtis%2C%20said%20that%20the%20firm%20is%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20developing%20an%20internal%20AI%20policy%20and%20expects%20to%20have%20certain%20AI%20tools%20integrated%20into%20the%20practice%20within%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20we're%20proceeding%20carefully%20we're%20very%20intentional%20in%20our%20plan%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Botero%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20feel%20that%20these%20tools%20will%20be%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Robinson%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20legal%20tech%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-legal-tech-startup-robin-ai-raise-series-b-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobin%20AI%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-chatbot-google-chatgpt-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%3C%2Fa%3E%20la